<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" border="0">
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="0031EC"><B><FONT color="FFFFFF">&nbsp;Subject:&nbsp;<b>event coverage</b></font></B></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="999999" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="999999" width="100%" valign="top"><tt><font color="000000">
Author:&nbsp;<b>Simon Lee</b>&nbsp;<br>
Date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;02-27-2001 23:08<br><br><BR>
Okay, this DPC coverage needs a little fixing.<BR>
<BR>
First of all, it took me days to find this cuz the icon for it is indistinguishable from just a background icon.  There should have been a text link.  <BR>
<BR>
Second, putting official coverage on a message board is extremely messy.  Official decktech updates should be text linked by round, each with the updated standings.  This appears to be because of inexperience with coverage.  Next time.  Message board is fine, just shouldn't be where you find the meat and potatoes.  If people want to chat, fine, just don't clog up the useful stuff.  It's like the produce at the supermarket being found on random shelves throughout the store.  Hey look, I finally found that carrot I was looking for behind a box of Cap'n Crunch.  Never did find the celery though...<BR>
<BR>
Third, while the final games synopsis was a good idea, the format prevented me from telling who was winning at any given point.  Include info on hand size and remaining cards.  Or just make it a video.<BR>
<BR>
MIA: complete deck breakdown.  I should know how many people played what deck.  If this info's here, I sure didn't see it (see first comment).  Attendence breakdown was good though.  Success rate of ALL decks as well.<BR>
<BR>
Also MIA: coverage on the "better officiating".  How many judges were there for 86 people?  How many penalties were given out.  What infractions occured.  Any rulings questions?<BR>
<BR>
First try so no worries but needs to be improved for Vegas.  Hope to be there.<BR>
</font></tt></td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
